All Star Musicals judge and Frozen actress Samantha Barks stunned fans as she attended the Olivier Awards at London’s Royal Albert Hall on Sunday night. The actress and singer wore a champagne gold dress with silver bead detailing as she walked the red carpet. The dress had a thigh-high split which allowed Samantha to show off her toned legs. She accessorised the look with matching silver heels. The 31-year-old wore her brunette locks in a loose, curly hairstyle. Samantha kept her jewellery simple, wearing silver drop earrings and rings, which ensured that all eyes were on her figure-hugging dress. The star, who is guest presenting a show on BBC Radio 2, shared her excitement on Twitter, writing: “Sunday Funday...!”